Wash and dry produce.

Peel and mince @garlic{2%cloves}(minced). Trim, peel, and cut @carrot{3%ounce}(peeled and cut into a small dice). Halve, peel, and cut @shallot{1}(peeled and diced into a small dice). Remove and discard any large stems from half the @kale{4%ounce}(chopped into bite-size pieces). Drain and rinse @cannellini beans{1%unit}. Quarter @lemon{1}(quartered).

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a large #pot{} over medium-high heat. Add @tofu{1}(crumbled) and cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned, ~{4%minutes}. Season with half the @Tuscan Heat Spice{1%tablespoon} (you'll use the rest in the next step), @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Add garlic and cook until lightly browned, ~{2%minutes}. Transfer tofu mixture to a #plate{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in same pot over medium heat. Add carrot and shallot; cook, stirring occasionally, until softened, ~{10%minutes}. (TIP: If veggies begin to brown too quickly, reduce heat to medium low.) Season with remaining Tuscan Heat Spice and a pinch of salt and pepper.

Stir in chopped kale, @chicken stock concentrate{3%unit}, 2 ½ cups water, and @salt{1/2%tsp}.

Cover pot, then increase heat to high and bring to a boil. Once boiling, uncover and stir in tofu mixture and beans.

Reduce heat to medium low and cover. Continue cooking until tofu is cooked through, ~{5%minutes} more.

Stir a big squeeze of lemon juice into soup. Taste and season with salt and pepper.

Divide soup between #bowls{}. Serve with remaining lemon wedges on the side.